		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Well, even so, the mod guy needs diagrams or pictures with big red marks on them or something so that even a first grader could do it.  We'd both rather he not screw up the converter and make me have to track down another one.  Talk to us like we've never dealt with NES hardware in our lives (because more than likely, we haven't) and give us big red markings on the picture. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />  He seems to have understood what you said, but big red marks are definitely his friends.  We'd need to know what to solder where, where to glue the metal piece so it doesn't screw everything up...basically anything vital.
<br />
<br />Sorry to be a pain, but really, we just want to make sure everything is done right.

		

